fella. I always thought... Pleasant

03:47.439 --> 03:48.521
personality? Yeah. He always... He always 
talked. I always remembered who I was. And Mrs.

03:57.451 --> 03:59.754
Harrington always a lady? I never did have a lot of 
contact with her, but I knew who she was. While you

04:10.046 --> 04:20.297
were an A&M undergraduate, were there any 
students here whose parents were famous, rich,

04:10.046 --> 04:20.297
important? No, but in Tarleton I did. Who? I don't 
know who they were. Oh. I taught, see I taught ag

04:30.152 --> 04:38.664
engineering in Tarleton from 35 to 37 for two 
years. And I taught and

04:38.684 --> 04:51.702
had to teach farm shop, all the ag engineering 
courses, what they had that they wanted, and So I

04:52.255 --> 05:02.165
was in that farm shop, and we had a lot of kids that 
came from the western part out there. And this

05:02.205 --> 05:07.611
young man, he knew what he was doing. And so I just 
asked him, I said, son, how big a farm do you have? He

05:15.879 --> 05:18.702
